Introduction¶

Dataset Description¶

This dataset collects information from 100k medical appointments in Brazil and is focused on the question of whether or not patients show up for their appointment. A number of characteristics about the patient are included in each row.

columns:¶

-PatientId: unique indentifier for each patient.¶

-AppointmentID: unique indentifier for each Appointment.¶

-Gender: sex of each patient and it contains two values : F: refers to female && M: refers to male.¶

-ScheduledDay: tells us on what day the patient set up their appointment.¶

-AppointmentDay: the date to go to the hospital.¶

-Age: the date of birth of each patient.¶

-Neighbourhood: indicates the location of the hospital.¶

-Scholarship: indicates whether or not the patient is enrolled in Brasilian welfare program Bolsa Família and it contains two values: 0 refers to be not enrolled and 1 refers to be enrolled.¶

-Hipertension: indicates whether or not the patient has high blood pressure.¶

-Diabetes: indicates whether or not the patient has Diabetes mellitus (is a chronic disease that impairs blood sugar regulation in the body) and it contains two values: 0 refers to not sick and 1 refers to sick.¶

-Alcoholism : indicates whether or not the patient is an addiction to drinking alcohol and it contains two values: 0 refers to not sick and 1 refers to sick.¶

-Handicap: indicates whether or not the patient has physical disability and it contains two values: 0 refers to not sick and 1 refers to sick.¶

-SMS_received: indicates whether or not the patient received message SMS and it contains two values: 0 refers to not sick and 1 refers to sick.¶

-No-show: it says ‘No’ if the patient showed up to their appointment, and ‘Yes’ if they did not show up.¶

Question(s) for Analysis¶

1)-Is there a relationship between No-show and Gender?¶

2)-Is there a relationship between No-show and the age of patient?¶

3)-Is there a relationship between No-show and location of the hospital?¶

4)-Is there a relationship between No-show and whether patient is enrolled in Brasilian welfare program Bolsa Família?¶

5)-Is there a relationship between No-show and whether the patient has Hypertension?¶

6)-Is there a relationship between No-show and whether the patient is Diabetic?¶

7)-Is there a relationship between No-show and whether the patient has Alcoholism?¶

8)-Is there a relationship between No-show and whether the patient has Handicap?¶

9)-Is there a relationship between No-show and whether the patient received SMS?¶

10)-Is there a relationship between No-show and days of week?¶

11)-Is there a relationship between No-show and the length of time between the day of booking and the day of the appointment?¶

12)-What factors are important for us to know in order to predict if a patient will show up for their scheduled appointment?¶

    '''axes design'''
    plt.title(f'The relation between {x} and No-show', fontsize=20)
    plt.xlabel(x, fontsize=20)
    plt.ylabel(y, fontsize=20)
    plt.legend(prop={'size': 20})
    plt.show()

Conclusions¶

-the attendance and absence rate for each gender is convergent, the gender doesn't have any effect on it.

-The No-show rate rises between 1 and 18 and reaches its highest level between 19 and 37, but it decreases between 38 and 55 to reach its lowest level between 56 and 115.

-there's a strong correlation between Neighbourhood and No-show.

-the No-show rate for enrolled patients or not enrolled patients is convergent, the Scholarship doesn't have any effect on it.

-Hypertension, Diabetes, Alcoholism, and Handicap don't have any effect on the No-show rate.

-the No-show rate of patients who received SMS is less than patients who not received SMS, it's strange!

-the No-show rate for patients every day of the week is convergent.

-the count of patients booking on the same day is the biggest And the longer the time between the day of booking and the day of the appointment,The higher the No-show rate.

limitations:¶

-there's no clear correlation between No-show and gender, chronic diseases,enrollment in Scholarship.
-the column 'Handicap' should have only values 0 or 1 which mean false or trueand not contains the number  of Handicap [2,3,4] for each patient
